WEBVTT

00:00.793 --> 00:02.419
[♪ opening theme song playing]

00:34.368 --> 00:38.622
JUJUTSU KAISEN

01:31.425 --> 01:34.053
[TENGEN] Nice to meet you,
child of Zen'in,

01:34.093 --> 01:35.804
Descendant of Michizane,

01:35.846 --> 01:37.598
Cursed Womb Death Painting,

01:37.639 --> 01:39.767
and Vessel of Sukuna.

01:39.808 --> 01:43.562
I guess you don't
have a greeting for me? Tengen.

01:43.604 --> 01:44.772
- [YUJI] So this...
- [MEGUMI] Thing.

01:44.813 --> 01:45.940
- [YUTA] This person.
- [CHOSO] Person?

01:45.981 --> 01:47.315
[MAKI] It's Tengen?

01:47.357 --> 01:49.693
[TENGEN] It's not
our first time meeting,

01:49.735 --> 01:51.528
Yuki Tsukumo.

01:51.862 --> 01:54.448
Tell me why you closed
the Tombs of the Star.

01:55.449 --> 01:59.160
[TENGEN] I was wary of you
being aligned with Kenjaku.

01:59.202 --> 02:02.915
I can't tell what's going on
in people's hearts, after all.

02:02.957 --> 02:04.083
[YUKI] Kenjaku?

02:05.584 --> 02:07.502
What was once Noritoshi Kamo,

02:07.544 --> 02:11.298
the sorcerer who's currently
inhabiting Suguru Geto's body.

02:11.339 --> 02:14.635
A net of compassion
and a rope of salvation.

02:14.676 --> 02:16.553
Wasn't even trying for sarcasm.

02:17.554 --> 02:19.974
You look nothing like
how I pictured you, Tengen.

02:20.015 --> 02:23.102
[MEGUMI] Ballsy to insert
himself into the conversation.

02:23.852 --> 02:26.605
Just because I'm immortal
doesn't make me ageless.

02:26.647 --> 02:29.524
You'd look like this too,
if you were 500 years old.

02:29.566 --> 02:30.692
[YUJI] Seriously?

02:31.693 --> 02:33.779
My aging has sped up

02:33.821 --> 02:35.489
ever since I failed
to assimilate

02:35.530 --> 02:38.199
with the Star Plasma Vessel
12 years ago.

02:38.241 --> 02:41.036
My identity as
an individual has vanished.

02:41.078 --> 02:43.122
Now you can consider
my existence

02:43.162 --> 02:44.748
as the world itself.

02:45.082 --> 02:46.792
[YUKI] So there wasn't
actually another

02:46.834 --> 02:48.710
Star Plasma Vessel back then?

02:49.962 --> 02:52.297
That explains
why there isn't a new voice.

02:53.256 --> 02:54.508
Excuse me.

02:54.549 --> 02:57.176
We came here
to learn Kenjaku's goal.

02:57.218 --> 03:00.014
And also to learn about
how to open the Prison Realm.

03:00.055 --> 03:02.265
Could you tell us
what you know about it?

03:04.101 --> 03:05.352
[TENGEN] Of course.

03:05.393 --> 03:07.688
But I must impose
one condition first,

03:07.729 --> 03:09.648
and it's non-negotiable.

03:09.690 --> 03:11.108
Yuta Okkotsu,

03:11.150 --> 03:12.484
Yuki Tsukumo,

03:12.526 --> 03:14.653
and the Cursed Womb
Death Painting.

03:14.695 --> 03:18.115
I'll need two of you three
to remain behind here.

03:18.365 --> 03:20.492
Remain behind and guard me.

03:20.534 --> 03:22.369
- [Megumi gasps]
- Guard you?

03:22.410 --> 03:23.954
You said you're immortal.

03:23.996 --> 03:26.165
Are you afraid
of being sealed or something?

03:26.205 --> 03:28.249
[YUKI] That isn't fair!

03:28.291 --> 03:30.169
Without telling us
why or how long

03:30.209 --> 03:31.252
we're guarding you.

03:39.011 --> 03:40.387
In that case...

03:43.098 --> 03:45.350
Let me speak of Kenjaku.

03:45.809 --> 03:46.810
KENJAKU'S OBJECTIVE

03:46.852 --> 03:48.729
That man's objective

03:48.770 --> 03:51.606
is to force the evolution
of mankind

03:51.648 --> 03:53.274
throughout all of Japan.

03:53.316 --> 03:54.317
THE EVOLUTION OF MANKIND
THROUGHOUT ALL JAPAN

03:54.359 --> 03:55.903
I heard about that.

03:56.570 --> 03:58.906
But how does he
actually intend to do it?

03:59.156 --> 04:01.033
And why didn't Kenjaku

04:01.075 --> 04:03.077
use your barriers
back when he could...

04:03.118 --> 04:04.494
IDLE TRANSFIGURATION

04:04.536 --> 04:06.538
...to turn everyone in Japan
into jujutsu sorcerers

04:06.580 --> 04:08.331
with Idle Transfiguration?

04:08.373 --> 04:09.624
IDLE TRANSFIGURATION

04:09.666 --> 04:10.333
THE EVOLUTION OF MANKIND
THROUGHOUT ALL JAPAN

04:10.375 --> 04:11.752
[TENGEN] For a simple reason.

04:11.793 --> 04:14.504
He lacked the cursed energy
to do so.

04:14.546 --> 04:16.882
The cursed energy
refined through Maelstrom

04:16.924 --> 04:18.884
can't return to the sorcerer.

04:18.926 --> 04:21.887
Besides, a cursed technique
involving people one at a time

04:21.929 --> 04:23.638
is far too inefficient.

04:23.680 --> 04:26.641
So Kenjaku's
new method of evolution

04:26.683 --> 04:29.144
is to assimilate
mankind with me.

04:29.186 --> 04:30.729
HOW?
ASSIMILATE MANKIND WITH TENGEN

04:33.648 --> 04:35.776
But wait.
I thought your assimilation--

04:35.817 --> 04:38.570
Should only be possible
with the Star Plasma Vessel.

04:38.612 --> 04:40.239
TENGEN - ORDINARY PERSON
ASSIMILATION IMPOSSIBLE

04:40.488 --> 04:42.074
Previously, that was true.

04:42.116 --> 04:43.491
STAR PLASMA VESSEL'S DEATH

04:43.533 --> 04:44.534
ASSIMILATION WITH THE STAR
PLASMA VESSEL PREVENTED

04:44.576 --> 04:47.204
But since I started evolving
12 years ago...

04:47.246 --> 04:49.873
TENGEN'S EVOLUTION

04:49.915 --> 04:51.290
...assimilation with someone

04:51.332 --> 04:53.210
other than
the Star Plasma Vessel

04:53.252 --> 04:54.335
is possible.

04:54.377 --> 04:55.921
ASSIMILATE MANKIND WITH TENGEN

04:55.963 --> 04:57.881
Even so, you're only one person.

04:58.381 --> 05:01.384
He still can't assimilate
with multiple people at once.

05:01.426 --> 05:02.594
[TENGEN] Wrong.

05:02.636 --> 05:04.303
Right now, the image
you are seeing of me

05:04.345 --> 05:06.181
is not my actual self.

05:06.223 --> 05:07.474
Now that I've evolved,

05:07.515 --> 05:09.977
my soul is
everywhere all the time.

05:10.518 --> 05:14.148
Like I said before, the world
itself is who I am now.

05:14.189 --> 05:15.732
People who assimilated with me

05:15.774 --> 05:18.401
would become something
more than a sorcerer.

05:18.443 --> 05:19.820
They'd become a new creature

05:19.861 --> 05:22.114
that at the same time
is both there and not there.

05:22.530 --> 05:24.323
It is because of
my barrier techniques

05:24.365 --> 05:26.701
that I was able to
retain my shape and reason

05:26.743 --> 05:28.369
after I started evolving.

05:28.411 --> 05:31.706
However, if mankind were
to begin evolving,

05:31.748 --> 05:34.417
even if only one person
went out of control...

05:34.459 --> 05:35.543
OUT OF CONTROL

05:35.585 --> 05:37.420
- ...the world would end.
- [YUKI] Why?

05:37.462 --> 05:40.548
[TENGEN] There would be no
boundaries between individuals.

05:40.590 --> 05:42.592
Evil would spread
to all instantly.

05:42.634 --> 05:45.012
The impurities
of 100 million people

05:45.053 --> 05:46.554
would flood the world.

05:46.596 --> 05:47.764
What happened in Tokyo

05:47.806 --> 05:50.100
would be recreated
on a worldwide scale.

05:50.642 --> 05:52.811
What would make him
wanna do something like that?

05:53.103 --> 05:55.354
[TENGEN] That, I do not know.

05:55.396 --> 05:58.733
As I said, there's no telling
what's inside people's hearts.

05:58.775 --> 06:00.277
WHY?
UNKNOWN

06:00.568 --> 06:01.903
If that's the case,

06:01.945 --> 06:03.822
as long as you
reject the assimilation,

06:03.864 --> 06:05.448
won't everything be fine?

06:05.490 --> 06:07.951
Now we're getting
to why I need guarding.

06:07.993 --> 06:09.286
Since I have evolved,

06:09.328 --> 06:11.705
my nature is closer to that
of a cursed spirit

06:11.746 --> 06:14.208
than it is to that
of a human being.

06:14.249 --> 06:18.795
So I can be targeted
by Cursed Spirit Manipulation.

06:19.462 --> 06:20.797
[all gasp]

06:21.673 --> 06:24.759
Considering Kenjaku's
enormous strength as a sorcerer,

06:24.801 --> 06:26.136
I would likely be absorbed

06:26.178 --> 06:28.180
the moment he made
contact with me.

06:28.680 --> 06:31.432
That's why my main body
is rejecting everything

06:31.474 --> 06:33.560
in the Tombs of the Star
right now.

06:34.228 --> 06:35.854
That's why you need guarding?

06:36.479 --> 06:37.647
Correct.

06:37.689 --> 06:39.482
Kenjaku is second
only to me in his skill

06:39.524 --> 06:40.817
with barrier techniques.

06:40.859 --> 06:42.777
I don't know when he'll
manage to break the seal

06:42.819 --> 06:44.571
on the Tombs of the Star.

06:44.988 --> 06:46.447
Why is this happening now?

06:46.489 --> 06:48.909
The Star Plasma Vessel
assimilation failed.

06:48.950 --> 06:50.493
You've been forced to evolve,

06:50.535 --> 06:53.080
so he wants to absorb you
with Cursed Energy Manipulation.

06:53.121 --> 06:56.875
It also seems Kenjaku
has connections to Sukuna.

06:56.917 --> 07:00.545
Which means he's been a sorcerer
for at least 1,000 years.

07:01.213 --> 07:03.298
So then, why now?

07:03.590 --> 07:06.093
Because myself,
the Star Plasma Vessel,

07:06.134 --> 07:07.677
and the Six Eyes

07:07.719 --> 07:10.931
are all connected by fate
and intertwined with each other.

07:10.972 --> 07:11.932
TENGEN - STAR PLASMA VESSEL
SIX EYES

07:12.349 --> 07:14.268
Twice in the past,
Kenjaku was stopped

07:14.309 --> 07:16.270
by the sorcerer
with the Six Eyes.

07:16.311 --> 07:17.812
The second time,
he was thorough.

07:17.854 --> 07:19.856
He killed both
the Star Plasma Vessel

07:19.898 --> 07:21.108
and the bearer of the Six Eyes

07:21.149 --> 07:22.943
within a month of their birth.

07:22.984 --> 07:25.904
Despite that, the Six Eyes
and the Star Plasma Vessel

07:25.946 --> 07:28.365
still appeared by the day
of my assimilation.

07:28.865 --> 07:31.159
After that, Kenjaku
altered his strategy

07:31.201 --> 07:33.870
to focus on sealing the Six Eyes
instead of killing him,

07:33.912 --> 07:36.290
as he began searching
for the Prison Realm.

07:36.664 --> 07:38.541
After all,
there can't be two people

07:38.583 --> 07:40.501
with the Six Eyes
at the same time.

07:41.002 --> 07:42.337
However, 12 years ago,

07:42.379 --> 07:44.339
something
unpredictable happened.

07:44.381 --> 07:46.133
Toji Zen'in intervened.

07:46.174 --> 07:47.592
UNPREDICTED EVENT
TOJI ZEN'IN INTERVENES

07:47.634 --> 07:50.387
He was physically gifted
through a Heavenly Pact.

07:50.429 --> 07:51.679
And he was unique among them

07:51.721 --> 07:54.557
for being completely free
from cursed energy.

07:55.183 --> 07:56.143
[MAKI] Mm.

07:56.184 --> 07:57.769
[MEGUMI] Hmm.

07:57.811 --> 08:00.439
[TENGEN] Since his Heavenly Pact
placed him outside of fate,

08:00.479 --> 08:03.358
he decided to destroy
the very fate that connected us.

08:03.400 --> 08:04.483
STAR PLASMA VESSEL'S DEATH

08:04.525 --> 08:05.860
Then, a young man with the power

08:05.902 --> 08:08.655
of Cursed Spirit Manipulation
appeared.

08:08.696 --> 08:11.532
Without even trying, he now had
all the necessary pieces

08:11.574 --> 08:13.160
except for the Prison Realm.

08:13.201 --> 08:14.453
CURSED SPIRIT MANIPULATION
STAR PLASMA VESSEL'S DEATH

08:14.493 --> 08:16.288
But, six years ago,

08:16.330 --> 08:19.458
the Prison Realm made its way
into Kenjaku's hands, as well.

08:19.498 --> 08:20.541
PRISON REALM

08:20.750 --> 08:22.501
If Kenjaku has the Prison Realm,

08:22.543 --> 08:24.838
then why is
this Culling Game being hosted?

08:25.172 --> 08:27.257
It's a warm-up
before assimilation.

08:27.715 --> 08:29.259
My assimilation with people

08:29.301 --> 08:31.845
other than the Star
Plasma Vessel is possible.

08:31.886 --> 08:33.888
But at the moment,
there's a high probability

08:33.930 --> 08:36.308
it will result in
something incomplete.

08:36.808 --> 08:39.978
The Culling Game uses
the cursed energy of the players

08:40.020 --> 08:42.647
and the boundaries
formed between the Colonies,

08:42.689 --> 08:45.066
in a ritual
to send this nation's people

08:45.108 --> 08:46.443
to the other side.

08:46.901 --> 08:49.112
He probably plans
to use that as a warm-up

08:49.154 --> 08:51.323
to start their assimilation
with me.

08:51.365 --> 08:52.491
MANKIND - TENGEN
THE CULLING GAME - WARM-UP

08:52.531 --> 08:54.659
However,
to establish that ritual,

08:54.701 --> 08:56.744
Kenjaku should've been forced

08:56.786 --> 08:58.497
to accept several pacts.

09:01.958 --> 09:04.627
One of those pacts
is that Kenjaku is not allowed

09:04.669 --> 09:07.422
to name himself
the Culling Game's Game Master.

09:07.464 --> 09:10.384
Unfortunately, that's
a disadvantage to you as well.

09:10.425 --> 09:15.389
Because it means that killing
Kenjaku won't end the game.

09:15.430 --> 09:17.765
Either all of the players
must die,

09:17.807 --> 09:20.894
or the players must all refuse
to participate and die.

09:21.311 --> 09:22.896
The rules specifically mention

09:22.937 --> 09:24.814
that nothing must
significantly hinder

09:24.856 --> 09:27.359
the continuation
of the Culling Game.

09:27.401 --> 09:29.528
An insurance policy
to prevent the ritual

09:29.568 --> 09:31.029
from being stopped.

09:31.071 --> 09:32.072
In that case...

09:32.113 --> 09:33.198
Yeah, right.

09:35.409 --> 09:37.994
All of us need to participate
in the Culling Game.

09:38.036 --> 09:40.579
And add a rule that creates
a way out of the game

09:40.621 --> 09:43.333
for Tsumiki and those
reluctant to participate.

09:45.252 --> 09:47.795
We need to free Gojo Sensei
at the same time.

09:48.129 --> 09:50.757
He could resolve this all
entirely on his own.

09:51.258 --> 09:52.467
ITADORI'S FRIENDS' OBJECTIVE

09:52.509 --> 09:54.302
CREATE A RULE
TO ESCAPE THE CULLING GAME

09:54.344 --> 09:55.554
FREE SATORU GOJO

09:55.594 --> 09:57.138
Uh, what do we do next?

09:57.180 --> 10:00.058
First, please decide
which of you will stay behind.

10:00.517 --> 10:01.560
[YUKI, CHOSO] I'll do it.

10:02.269 --> 10:03.270
I'll stay.

10:03.311 --> 10:04.603
[YUJI, MEGUMI] Huh?

10:04.645 --> 10:06.523
Yuji, you are absolutely
going to need the help

10:06.565 --> 10:08.816
of either Okkotsu
or that woman,

10:08.858 --> 10:10.402
Noritoshi Kamo.

10:10.444 --> 10:12.487
If Kenjaku comes,
that's all the more reason

10:12.529 --> 10:13.863
for me to guard Tengen.

10:14.573 --> 10:16.783
I must do so because
slaying him would mean

10:16.824 --> 10:18.452
saving my younger brothers.

10:18.493 --> 10:21.455
[YUKI] I'm still not finished
talking with Tengen just yet.

10:21.496 --> 10:24.040
Does that sound okay, Okkotsu?

10:24.082 --> 10:27.335
Yeah, I don't wanna be
separated from everyone anymore.

10:30.589 --> 10:31.839
Thank you.

10:32.715 --> 10:33.758
Now this.

10:37.053 --> 10:39.556
This is the Back
of the Prison Realm.

10:39.598 --> 10:42.641
If you plan to free Satoru Gojo,

10:42.683 --> 10:43.893
you'll need it.

10:43.935 --> 10:45.270
The back?

10:45.312 --> 10:46.687
First I've heard of it.

10:46.729 --> 10:48.273
Like a back door?

10:48.315 --> 10:49.608
That's right.

10:49.648 --> 10:51.485
Before Kenjaku found it,

10:51.526 --> 10:54.195
the Prison Realm was
outside of my barriers.

10:54.237 --> 10:55.989
Probably somewhere abroad.

10:57.449 --> 10:59.284
I thought
keeping this Back sealed

10:59.326 --> 11:01.578
would obscure
the presence of the Front,

11:01.620 --> 11:02.912
but it didn't work.

11:03.455 --> 11:07.542
Satoru Gojo is also sealed away
within this back gate.

11:07.584 --> 11:10.044
What? Then let's open it
and let him out!

11:10.086 --> 11:12.464
[TENGEN] No,
the authority to open the gates

11:12.506 --> 11:14.673
rests with the owner
of the Front.

11:14.715 --> 11:15.883
Kenjaku.

11:15.925 --> 11:17.969
In order to break this one open,

11:18.011 --> 11:20.180
you need either
the Inverted Spear of Heaven

11:20.221 --> 11:23.057
that can force the cancellation
of cursed techniques,

11:23.099 --> 11:25.143
or something
that can disrupt and cancel out

11:25.185 --> 11:27.312
the effects of
a cursed technique.

11:27.354 --> 11:29.230
The Black Rope could do it.

11:30.482 --> 11:33.985
However, 12 years ago,
Satoru Gojo either sealed

11:34.027 --> 11:37.531
the Inverted Spear of Heaven
abroad or destroyed it.

11:37.572 --> 11:39.616
Ugh! Why would you
do that, Sensei?

11:39.658 --> 11:41.284
[TENGEN]
And last year, the black rope

11:41.326 --> 11:43.744
was also completely
frayed by Gojo.

11:43.786 --> 11:45.830
Ugh! What was he thinking?

11:46.122 --> 11:47.706
[chuckles]

11:47.748 --> 11:49.250
Reminds me of Miguel.

11:49.292 --> 11:50.502
We went to Africa

11:50.544 --> 11:52.629
looking for some more
of that Black Rope.

11:52.671 --> 11:54.172
So that's where you were.

11:54.214 --> 11:55.674
Please tell me you found it.

11:56.132 --> 11:58.259
Sorry, but it was
a complete waste of effort.

11:58.301 --> 12:01.262
- They said it's all gone.
- Huh?

12:01.304 --> 12:02.597
Is there another way?

12:02.639 --> 12:04.224
[TENGEN] There is.

12:04.599 --> 12:07.726
Among the players participating
in the upcoming Culling Game,

12:08.061 --> 12:10.230
there's a sorcerer
from 1,000 years ago

12:10.271 --> 12:12.148
who calls herself "Angel."

12:12.190 --> 12:19.197
ANGEL

12:19.573 --> 12:21.866
Her cursed technique
can extinguish

12:21.908 --> 12:23.910
any other cursed technique.

12:24.869 --> 12:27.788
HANA KURUSU

12:27.830 --> 12:30.917
EPISODE 50
ABOUT THE CULLING GAME

12:31.459 --> 12:34.212
[MEGUMI] Extinguish
any cursed technique?

12:34.546 --> 12:35.880
[TENGEN] Yes.

12:35.922 --> 12:38.132
And Angel's cursed technique
also has the power

12:38.174 --> 12:40.134
to open the Back
of the Prison Realm.

12:41.010 --> 12:43.137
Can you tell us
where she is right now?

12:43.513 --> 12:46.433
She's in the Colony
on the east side of Tokyo.

12:46.474 --> 12:48.602
The barriers
of the Culling Game reject me.

12:48.643 --> 12:51.187
I'm afraid I don't have
any more information than that.

12:51.229 --> 12:52.272
[gasps]

12:56.901 --> 12:59.571
[TENGEN] Let's start
going over things from there.

12:59.613 --> 13:02.198
There are 10 Colonies
across Japan.

13:02.240 --> 13:04.117
They are linked together
by barriers

13:04.158 --> 13:07.746
designed to ferry the country's
people over to the other side.

13:07.786 --> 13:09.372
[AKARI] Crossing a river
or other border,

13:09.414 --> 13:11.916
acts that symbolize
crossing over to the afterlife,

13:11.958 --> 13:14.377
these carry important
meanings in sorcery.

13:14.419 --> 13:16.671
Oh. It's like
with Yasohachi Bridge!

13:16.713 --> 13:17.796
YASOHACHI BRIDGE'S RIVER
OTHER SIDE - COLONIES' BARRIERS

13:31.770 --> 13:34.188
The Jujutsu Society's barrier?

13:34.230 --> 13:36.065
So, is Hokkaido excluded?

13:36.107 --> 13:37.567
[TENGEN] It is.

13:37.609 --> 13:41.028
That land is already established
as a vast sacred ground.

13:41.446 --> 13:43.698
I guess that's
"the challenging land" for you.

13:44.365 --> 13:46.451
[TENGEN]
"Ferry them to the other side"

13:46.493 --> 13:48.369
may sound a bit dramatic,

13:48.411 --> 13:50.246
but everyone in Japan was cursed

13:50.288 --> 13:53.291
in preparation
for the upcoming assimilation.

13:58.630 --> 14:00.465
WARM-UP COMPLETE
THE CULLING GAME

14:00.507 --> 14:01.882
[MEGUMI]
Tell me about this ritual.

14:01.924 --> 14:03.593
How long will it take
to complete?

14:04.010 --> 14:05.804
Depends on the Culling Game.

14:05.844 --> 14:07.972
My guess, it's over
in two months.

14:09.349 --> 14:10.767
1: PLAYERS MUST GO TO A COLONY
WITHIN 19 DAYS

14:10.809 --> 14:11.934
AND PLEDGE THEIR PARTICIPATION
IN THE CULLING GAME.

14:11.976 --> 14:14.646
It is currently 9:00 a.m.
on the 9th of November.

14:14.688 --> 14:17.398
Nine days since the players
awakened as sorcerers,

14:17.440 --> 14:20.151
which happened October 31st,
around midnight.

14:20.777 --> 14:23.780
That gives us about 10 days
and 15 hours to go

14:24.238 --> 14:26.240
before Tsumiki's forced to play.

14:26.282 --> 14:27.950
REMAINING TIME UNTIL TSUMIKI
MUST ENTER THE CULLING GAME

14:27.992 --> 14:30.745
OBTAIN 100 POINTS AND ADD A RULE
ALLOWING PEOPLE TO ESCAPE.

14:31.912 --> 14:33.414
2: PLAYERS BREACHING RULE SHALL
BE STRIPPED OF THEIR TECHNIQUE.

14:33.456 --> 14:34.999
Tengen, you said before

14:35.041 --> 14:37.377
that people would die
if they refused to participate.

14:37.418 --> 14:38.877
That's right.

14:39.337 --> 14:41.381
They get stripped
of their technique, huh?

14:41.422 --> 14:43.049
I believe that rule also applies

14:43.090 --> 14:45.176
to any sorcerers
joining in later.

14:45.968 --> 14:48.388
If that's the case,
the stripping isn't being done

14:48.429 --> 14:51.057
by Idle Transfiguration.

14:51.098 --> 14:52.891
It's not a pact either.

14:52.933 --> 14:55.603
Because it says "stripped,"
not "prohibited."

14:55.645 --> 14:58.022
[exhales]
So that probably means

14:58.064 --> 15:01.067
it'll be doing something
to the brain by force.

15:01.108 --> 15:04.320
And it's better for the rules if
being stripped means death, too.

15:04.362 --> 15:07.365
Otherwise, everyone
would refuse to participate.

15:07.657 --> 15:09.992
It's just as Shoko anticipated.

15:10.034 --> 15:11.910
But that also means
there's no risk

15:11.952 --> 15:14.789
to sorcerers without any
cursed technique like me.

15:15.289 --> 15:17.208
And what'll happen to Panda?

15:17.250 --> 15:18.917
Does he even have a brain?

15:20.211 --> 15:22.505
3: NON-PLAYERS SHALL BECOME
PLAYERS UPON ENTERING A COLONY

15:22.547 --> 15:23.840
About this rule,

15:23.882 --> 15:25.800
what does it mean
for the ordinary people

15:25.842 --> 15:27.844
who are in the Colony
from the start?

15:28.177 --> 15:29.387
It means anyone who wants

15:29.429 --> 15:31.639
will be granted at least
one chance to leave.

15:31.681 --> 15:33.057
For real?

15:33.099 --> 15:34.809
How awfully generous.

15:35.393 --> 15:37.604
[TENGEN] There are
no stipulations in the rules

15:37.645 --> 15:40.147
about leaving
or entering Colonies.

15:40.189 --> 15:42.776
They were probably trying
to stimulate the Culling Game

15:42.817 --> 15:45.069
by giving players
a clear first-time goal

15:45.111 --> 15:48.239
of leaving the Colony
with their lives intact.

15:48.281 --> 15:51.200
In order to keep the players
inside for the duration,

15:51.242 --> 15:54.203
the premise that players entered
of their own free will

15:54.245 --> 15:56.080
is extremely important.

15:56.122 --> 15:58.917
Ino mentioned that thing about
adjusting the barrier strength.

15:59.876 --> 16:01.711
4: PLAYERS WILL RECEIVE POINTS

16:01.753 --> 16:04.130
UPON ENDING THE LIFE
OF ANOTHER PLAYER.

16:04.171 --> 16:05.840
ENDING THE LIFE

16:05.882 --> 16:08.092
[Yuji exhales]

16:08.134 --> 16:09.886
5: POINTS SHALL BE DESIGNATED
BASED ON THE VALUE

16:09.928 --> 16:11.387
THAT THE GAME MASTER
GIVES THEIR LIFE

16:11.429 --> 16:14.140
Using "fundamentally" in a rule.
Why make it confusing?

16:14.181 --> 16:16.183
- [Megumi grunts]
- Eh, is something wrong?

16:16.601 --> 16:17.894
[MEGUMI] It's nothing.

16:17.936 --> 16:20.438
Tengen, who is this Game Master?

16:20.480 --> 16:21.564
GAME MASTER

16:21.980 --> 16:23.524
[TENGEN] Every individual player

16:23.566 --> 16:26.402
is given a shikigami
called "Kogane."

16:26.820 --> 16:30.281
To be precise,
Kogane isn't the Game Master.

16:30.323 --> 16:31.783
It's an interface.

16:31.825 --> 16:34.786
It's best to think of
the Culling Game itself

16:34.828 --> 16:36.454
as the Game Master.

16:37.622 --> 16:39.248
Okay, I got it.

16:40.207 --> 16:41.542
6: BY SPENDING 100 POINTS,
PLAYERS MAY NEGOTIATE

16:41.584 --> 16:42.293
WITH THE GAME MASTER TO ADD
AN ADDITIONAL RULE

16:42.335 --> 16:44.086
So we can add, but

16:44.128 --> 16:47.005
we're not allowed
to eliminate any existing rules.

16:47.047 --> 16:48.591
[Yuji groans]

16:48.633 --> 16:51.427
Maybe we'll be able to come up
with some kind of workaround.

16:53.011 --> 16:55.222
7: THE GAME MASTER MUST APPROVE
ANY ADDITIONAL RULES

16:55.264 --> 16:56.474
How's that allowed?

16:57.517 --> 16:58.685
Yeah, right.

16:58.726 --> 17:01.019
It leans too heavily
on their own judgment.

17:01.354 --> 17:02.396
No.

17:02.438 --> 17:04.022
You should expect
a fair decision

17:04.064 --> 17:05.942
when it comes to all challenges.

17:05.984 --> 17:07.861
They're already
subjecting the players

17:07.902 --> 17:09.529
to such stringent rules.

17:09.570 --> 17:11.489
Jujutsu sorcery
would not allow them

17:11.531 --> 17:14.283
to show more favoritism
towards Kenjaku.

17:15.159 --> 17:16.577
8: PLAYERS WHO DO NOT SHOW
A CHANGE IN POINTS

17:16.619 --> 17:17.745
WITHIN 19 DAYS SHALL BE
STRIPPED OF THEIR TECHNIQUE.

17:17.787 --> 17:19.956
So then, does that mean
I'll be killing people again?

17:20.540 --> 17:21.833
Maybe not.

17:21.875 --> 17:23.292
I have a few ideas.

17:26.587 --> 17:29.465
[MAKI] We've managed to organize
our information for now.

17:29.507 --> 17:31.634
That just leaves the roles
for each of us.

17:31.676 --> 17:33.093
FUTURE ACTIONS

17:33.469 --> 17:35.555
Yuki and Choso will remain here.

17:35.763 --> 17:36.890
They'll guard Tengen.

17:36.931 --> 17:38.224
CHOSO - YUKI TSUKUMO
GUARD TENGEN

17:38.725 --> 17:41.143
Meanwhile, I need to return
to the Zen'in house

17:41.185 --> 17:42.729
to get their cursed tools.

17:43.813 --> 17:45.314
Right after Gojo was sealed,

17:45.356 --> 17:47.859
the Kamo and Zen'in clans
both took their cursed tools

17:47.901 --> 17:50.028
out of Jujutsu High's
forbidden vault.

17:50.068 --> 17:52.864
However, Megumi's now
the head of the Zen'in clan.

17:52.906 --> 17:55.825
- Huh?
- I'll explain it to you later.

17:56.158 --> 17:59.286
So we're free to rummage through
the Zen'in's forbidden vault.

17:59.328 --> 18:02.456
But, before that, Tengen?

18:02.790 --> 18:06.920
I know what you want.
It's Juzo Kumiya's atelier.

18:06.961 --> 18:08.337
Yes, thank you.

18:08.379 --> 18:10.506
Once I'm finished,
I'll look for Panda.

18:10.548 --> 18:13.175
After that, I'll help
deal with the Culling Game.

18:13.217 --> 18:14.594
And you, Yuta?

18:15.177 --> 18:17.555
I'll enter a Colony and
participate in the Culling Game.

18:17.597 --> 18:18.973
The sooner, the better.

18:19.015 --> 18:20.975
Before Tsumiki and
Fushiguro enter,

18:21.017 --> 18:22.727
I want to know as much as I can.

18:22.769 --> 18:24.771
Then I'll be
thoroughly prepared.

18:25.521 --> 18:26.564
Thank you.

18:27.231 --> 18:29.734
It'll mean acting
on my own once again.

18:29.776 --> 18:33.153
However, in order to prevent us
from clashing with each other,

18:33.195 --> 18:36.532
and in case something does
happen to Tsumiki out there,

18:36.574 --> 18:38.451
I'll avoid the nearby Colonies.

18:39.535 --> 18:41.245
We should be aware
that the Colonies

18:41.287 --> 18:42.413
might cut off reception,

18:42.455 --> 18:44.665
so I might be
out of contact for a while.

18:44.999 --> 18:46.333
[both gasp]

18:46.375 --> 18:48.502
If Sukuna appears
and takes control of me again,

18:48.544 --> 18:50.004
I need you to kill me.

18:50.046 --> 18:51.464
Having Okkotsu near Itadori
would keep Fushiguro safe,

18:51.505 --> 18:52.465
but it would be more efficient
for Okkotsu to act alone.

18:52.506 --> 18:54.508
- [groans]
- Don't worry about that now.

18:55.009 --> 18:56.218
It's gonna be fine.

18:56.260 --> 18:58.679
If that happens,
you can have him kill you.

18:58.721 --> 19:00.014
After I die.

19:00.056 --> 19:02.600
Yeah, well, I'm trying
to avoid that situation.

19:03.643 --> 19:05.019
Maki.

19:05.061 --> 19:06.520
Right.

19:06.562 --> 19:09.273
I want you two to meet up
with Kinji like we planned.

19:09.315 --> 19:10.357
Kinji?

19:10.399 --> 19:11.901
Kinji Hakari.

19:11.943 --> 19:14.070
The third-year guy
that got suspended.

19:14.570 --> 19:17.323
We're shorthanded,
so it's all hands on deck.

19:17.364 --> 19:19.325
Do whatever it takes
to recruit him.

19:19.366 --> 19:20.994
[YUJI] Is he strong, at least?

19:21.702 --> 19:23.203
He's a bit erratic,

19:23.245 --> 19:26.040
but if he gets into it, he can
be even stronger than I am.

19:26.082 --> 19:27.500
That is impossible.

19:30.003 --> 19:31.378
KENJAKU'S OBJECTIVE (ROAD MAP)

19:35.424 --> 19:36.634
THE EVOLUTION OF MANKIND
THROUGHOUT ALL JAPAN

19:36.676 --> 19:38.011
THE CULLING GAME'S OBJECTIVE

19:41.179 --> 19:42.849
ASSIMILATE MANKIND WITH TENGEN

19:42.890 --> 19:43.933
ITADORI'S FRIENDS' MISSION

19:48.729 --> 19:51.524
EACH PERSON'S ACTIONS

19:51.565 --> 19:53.151
PARTICIPATE IN THE CULLING GAME
REMAIN IN THE TOMBS OF THE STAR

20:06.706 --> 20:07.790
Choso!

20:08.457 --> 20:10.376
I wanna thank you
for all the help.

20:11.627 --> 20:13.004
Don't die out there.

20:17.967 --> 20:19.844
[Choso crying]

20:19.886 --> 20:22.220
- Are you really crying?
- [CHOSO] Shh. Shh.

20:28.394 --> 20:31.229
[yawns]

20:32.690 --> 20:35.193
Uh, thanks for coming.

20:35.735 --> 20:38.529
- [scattered applause]
- [MAN] Takaba!

20:38.571 --> 20:41.074
How long are you
gonna keep doin' that crap?

20:41.115 --> 20:43.784
Cut it out! [sighs]
You're making me depressed.

20:43.826 --> 20:45.285
The audience too.

20:45.327 --> 20:47.914
[TAKABA] Yeah, I know.
[sniffles]

20:47.955 --> 20:49.373
[MAN] How old are you now?

20:49.874 --> 20:51.209
35 years old.

20:51.249 --> 20:53.044
Just give it up already!

20:53.086 --> 20:55.546
Our industry,
it's full of late-bloomers

20:55.588 --> 20:58.298
who suddenly make it big
for no good reason.

20:58.340 --> 20:59.842
But not a single one

20:59.884 --> 21:02.929
out of the blue suddenly
actually became funnier!

21:02.970 --> 21:04.262
They were already funny people

21:04.304 --> 21:06.933
waiting patiently
to be discovered.

21:06.974 --> 21:08.976
That ain't the case for you.

21:09.018 --> 21:10.436
Look what happened to Tokyo.

21:10.477 --> 21:12.146
No one's gonna think ill of you.

21:12.188 --> 21:14.732
Go do something
you're actually suited for.

21:14.774 --> 21:17.777
- [door opens, closes]
- [sobbing]

21:18.527 --> 21:20.529
I always thought
you were kind of funny.

21:20.571 --> 21:22.406
- You always made me laugh.
- Huh?

21:23.783 --> 21:24.992
You mean it, Ken?

21:25.034 --> 21:27.494
Both you and him
have the wrong idea.

21:28.286 --> 21:31.165
There are people who ain't funny
that still make it big.

21:35.211 --> 21:37.046
Are they one-gag comics
like me, though?

21:37.088 --> 21:38.547
Absolutely not.

21:38.589 --> 21:41.884
There are two types of comedians
that manage to stay big.

21:41.926 --> 21:44.011
Comedians who are always funny,

21:44.053 --> 21:45.345
and comedians who can go ahead

21:45.387 --> 21:48.099
and delude themselves
into believing they are.

21:51.518 --> 21:52.770
[exhales]

21:54.438 --> 21:56.232
So which type are you?

21:56.274 --> 21:58.484
[TAKABA] Well, I'd like to think
I'm 50-50. [chuckles]

21:58.525 --> 22:01.821
But in actuality, it's probably
a lot closer to 70-30.

22:01.862 --> 22:03.656
Uh... [inhales sharply]

22:03.697 --> 22:06.200
- [♪ suspenseful music playing]
- 50-50 or 70-30!

22:06.867 --> 22:09.870
CULLING GAME PLAYER
FUMIHIKO TAKABA

22:10.328 --> 22:12.456
[♪ closing theme song playing]

23:40.961 --> 23:43.297
- [MAKI] Mai, let's get started.
- [MAI] Why did you come here?

23:43.339 --> 23:45.549
[NAOYA] I think I'll bully you
like I used to, remember?

23:45.591 --> 23:46.759
[MEGUMI] Please do it, Maki.

23:46.800 --> 23:49.011
[MAI] You are me, and I am you.

23:49.053 --> 23:50.554
[MAKI AND MAI'S MOTHER]
I gave birth to you.

23:50.596 --> 23:52.223
[OGI] Absolutely ridiculous.

23:52.681 --> 23:53.849
[MAI] Destroy everything.

23:53.891 --> 23:54.975
NEXT EPISODE
PERFECT PREPARATION
